question.title: AWS ElasticBeanStalk
question.body:
I'm trying to deploy a Java app with Elasticbeanstalk and CodePipeline. The elasticbeanstalk works well but when I try to deploy using a pipeline shows the next error:

Deployment completed, but with errors: During an aborted deployment, some instances may have deployed the new application version. To ensure all instances are running the same version, re-deploy the appropriate application version

I've configured my VPC with a public subnet and a Gateway but the error persists.

What could be wrong?

Thanks
